{
  "info": {
    "name": "Kong Gateway - Rate Limit and Request Size Tests",
    "_postman_id": "d01f58db-43ca-42d4-8af9-27d9c0e1f4c2",
    "description": "Postman collection for testing the DB-less Kong gateway in front of `app.py` (port 8000) and `artist_app.py` (port 8001).\n\nRun the backend apps first:\n```\npython3 app.py\n```\nThen start Kong:\n```\ndocker compose up -d kong\n```\n\nPorts:\n- Kong proxy: `http://localhost:9000`\n- Kong Admin API: `http://localhost:9001`\n\nRequired assignment scenarios included explicitly:\n- 10 rapid requests (>5/s) -> `429 Too Many Requests`\n- POST with 2 MB body -> `413 Payload Too Large`\n- No Authorization header -> `401 Unauthorized`\n- Valid admin credentials -> `200 OK` with higher per-consumer quota",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "kong_proxy_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:9000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "kong_admin_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:9001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "artist_basic_user",
      "value": "admin",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "artist_basic_pass",
      "value": "secret123",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "artist_admin_apikey",
      "value": "artist-admin-key",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "artist_readonly_apikey",
      "value": "artist-readonly-key",
